Title : Francisco Polti Santillán
Text : '''Francisco Polti Santillán''' (November 17, 1938) is a [[prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]]. He served as [[bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Santo Tomé|Santo Tomé]] from 1994 until 2006, and as bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Santiago del Estero|Santiago del Estero]] from 2006 until his retirement in 2013.

== Life ==
Born in [[Santiago del Estero]], Polti Santillán became a member of [[Opus Dei]]. He was [[Holy Orders|ordained]] to the [[Priesthood (Catholic Church)|priesthood]] on August 11, 1963.

On July 13, 1994, he was appointed [[bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Santo Tomé|Santo Tomé]]. Polti Santillán received his [[Bishop (Catholic Church)|episcopal consecration]] on the following August 22 from [[Antonio Cardinal Quarracino|Antonio Quarracino]], archbishop of Buenos Aires, with archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Santa Fe de la Vera Cruz|Santa Fe de la Vera Cruz]], [[Edgardo Gabriel Storni]], archbishop emeritus of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Corrientes|Corrientes]], [[Fortunato Antonio Rossi]], archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Corrientes|Corrientes]], [[Domingo Salvador Castagna]], and bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Posadas|Posadas]], [[Alfonso Delgado Evers]], serving as [[Consecrator|co-consecrators]]. He was installed on the following September 11.

On May 17, 2006, he was appointed [[bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Santiago del Estero|Santiago del Estero]], where he was installed on the following July 22. He resigned on December 23, 2013, when he reached the age of 75 year, the age of retirement for bishops.

